# Cloudflare Pages _headers
# Audit follow-up F2 (2026-05-10): Content-Security-Policy + transport
# security headers for the Ophis SPA. Applies to every path.
#
# CSP POSTURE DECISION: the three broad directives (frame-ancestors *,
# script-src 'unsafe-eval', connect-src/img-src https:) are deliberate,
# reviewed-and-accepted tradeoffs with documented revisit triggers — see
# docs/operations/csp-posture.md before tightening or loosening them.
#
# Notes:
# - script-src: 'self' + 'wasm-unsafe-eval' + 'unsafe-eval'. The
#   'unsafe-eval' is needed because cowswap's token-list validator
#   (libs/tokens/validateTokenList.ts) uses ajv@6 which compiles
#   schemas at runtime — without it, custom-token-list loading
#   silently fails. Upstream cowswap CSP makes the same allowance
#   (apps/cowswap-frontend/vercel.ts:51-53). NO 'unsafe-inline' on
#   scripts: Vite production bundles have no inline <script> tags.
#   The upstream CoW GTM call stays disabled; Ophis GA4 (gtag.js) is
#   loaded from https://www.googletagmanager.com by a BUNDLED module
#   (src/ophis/analytics/initGa4.ts), not an inline snippet, so no
#   'unsafe-inline' is needed. GA4 beacons to *.google-analytics.com
#   are already covered by `connect-src https:`.
#   KNOWN + INTENTIONAL (do NOT "fix" by loosening script-src): once
#   gtag.js runs (production host only, since initGa4 is gated to
#   swap.ophis.fi), Google's own gtag code injects a couple of RUNTIME
#   inline <script>s, which this CSP correctly blocks. That surfaces as
#   ~2 benign, intermittent CSP console errors on swap.ophis.fi. They are
#   accepted on purpose: GA4 core measurement is unaffected (dataLayer +
#   first-party beacons via the /938g Tag Gateway still flow), and the
#   blocked scripts are non-essential gtag internals. Adding 'unsafe-inline'
#   would gut the policy, and hashing Google's inline scripts is a
#   maintenance treadmill (the hashes rotate whenever gtag updates).
# - style-src includes 'unsafe-inline' because styled-components
#   injects runtime style tags. Standard practice.
# - connect-src and img-src use the broad `https:` / `wss:` schemes
#   because cowswap reaches dozens of RPC providers, subgraphs,
#   token-list CDNs, wallet-connect relays, etc. Tightening to an
#   explicit allow-list is brittle and would routinely break on
#   cowswap subtree pulls. Acceptable trade-off: still blocks
#   mixed-content + non-HTTPS exfiltration.
# - frame-ancestors *: the Ophis swap surface is an EMBEDDABLE WIDGET
#   (see docs/widget.md + @ophis/widget-react). Integrators load
#   swap.ophis.fi in an iframe on their own origin, so third-party
#   framing must be allowed. This matches the upstream CoW posture
#   (swap.cow.fi ships frame-ancestors *; the widget is the product).
#   Clickjacking is mitigated structurally, NOT by frame-busting:
#   every value-moving action (connect, token approval, order
#   signature) completes only via a wallet-rendered popup OUTSIDE the
#   frame, showing the real tx/typed-data — a redress overlay cannot
#   forge it. In-frame-only state (slippage, theme) moves no funds.
#   The widget<->host channel is separately origin-gated by the
#   postMessage transport (libs/iframe-transport), not by CSP.
#   NOTE: because this is a hash-routed SPA (one origin, '#/.../widget'
#   route), CF _headers cannot scope framing to the widget path alone;
#   the whole swap app is therefore embeddable, as it is for CoW.
# - object-src 'none' kills <embed>/<object>/<applet>.
# - upgrade-insecure-requests forces any plain-http URL the bundle
#   contains to be fetched over HTTPS.
#
# To debug CSP violations after a deploy: check browser DevTools
# Console + Network for blocked-by-CSP entries. If a legitimate
# resource is blocked, add its origin to the matching directive.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' 'unsafe-eval' https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://www.googletagmanager.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com data:; img-src 'self' data: blob: https:; connect-src 'self' https: wss:; frame-src 'self' https:; frame-ancestors *; worker-src 'self' blob:; manifest-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://formspree.io; object-src 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  # NO X-Frame-Options: the swap surface is an embeddable widget and must
  # load cross-origin on integrator sites. X-Frame-Options cannot express
  # an open/any-origin allowance (only DENY / SAMEORIGIN), and a browser
  # that honours a stale SAMEORIGIN here would BLOCK the very embedding the
  # widget exists for. Framing control is therefore expressed solely by the
  # CSP `frame-ancestors *` directive above (the modern, sole successor to
  # XFO); clickjacking is mitigated structurally by out-of-frame wallet
  # signing, as documented in the Notes block. (supersedes audit P3)
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), midi=(), interest-cohort=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin-allow-popups
  X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: on

# Long-cache hashed assets (Vite emits content-hashes in filenames).
/static/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Self-hosted token + chain logos — small, cacheable, never change
# content under a given filename.
/logos/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000, immutable

# HTML / index — no-cache so deploys propagate immediately.
/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate

# emergency.js is the boot script — it runs synchronously before the
# SPA bundle and controls subdomain redirect + HashRouter path-to-hash
# rewriting. It MUST always be fresh; a stale cached version can break
# routing for hours. CF Pages default was 4h, which caused PR #261
# (deep-link hash redirect) to take effect inconsistently for users
# with cached versions. Force revalidation on every load.
/emergency.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate

# /docs is a separate static HTML page (not the SPA). Short max-age
# so doc edits propagate within an hour, but still cacheable so we
# get crawler-friendly response times.
/docs
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
/docs/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
/docs/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
